                "data": [
                    {
                        "type": "paragraph",
                        "data": "Terminations must respect complex rules and the rules of an employeeâ€™s employment country. The off-boarding is always handled by the Employer with the primary stakeholders. It may include ad-hoc fees as well as required or recommended steps on specific termination cases."
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "paragraph",
                        "data": "Employee dismissal must be according to the Labor and Standards Act (LSA). Both employer and employee are required to provide notice or payment in lieu. Any non taken holidays, payments, or benefits must be paid upon termination."
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "title": "Notice Period",
                "data": [
                    {
                        "type": "paragraph",
                        "data": "The minimum notice period is 0 days and will be increased according to the length of the employment."
                    },
